@node "examples" "example numbers"
@{i}@{u}Examples@{ui}@{uu}

 DECODING

  In Decode mode, a full seven digit number is required.  Type in
  one of the following numbers and press start to obtain a full list.

   3286468         eat mint
   9226261         cab man
   6244464         nagging

 ENCODING

  In Encode mode, any entry is acceptable.  If a number cannot be
  found, a ? will be substitued.  The ? means any number would
  work in that position (see below).

   callsue         2255783
   amigas          264427?   where ? can be 0,1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8 or 9
@endnode

@node "History" "History"
@{i}@{u}History@{ui}@{uu}

 VERSION    RELEASE DATE         COMMENTS


  V 1.0       07/01/97        Initial release.

  V 1.1       07/15/97        Added additional comments for help
