@node "Requirements" "Requirements"
@{i}@{u}Requirements@{ui}@{uu}

  PhoneSpell doesn't have any special requirements other than OS 3.0 or
higher.
@endnode

@node "Using" "How To Use"
@{i}@{u}Usage@{ui}@{uu}

 Using PhoneSpell is, hopefully, quite easy.

 PhoneSpell may be started from the WorkBench or the CLI.  From WorkBench,
 just doubleclick on its icon.  From a shell type in

 run PhoneSpell

 To @{b}@{u}DECODE@{ub}@{uu} a number: Just type in the number you wish to have decoded into
 the @{"phone number entry gadget" link "Layout" 0} and then click on the @{"Start gadget" link "Layout" 0}.  The
 number entered must be a valid number.  If everything is correct, the
 program will begin to decode your number.  When the decoding is finished,
 the appropriate gadgets are updated.  The results are stored in five
 separate @{"lists" link "Layout" 0}.  Each list is displayed in the @{"listview gadget" link "Layout" 0} by
 selecting it with the @{"list toggle" link "Layout" 0} gadget.

 To @{b}@{u}ENCODE@{ub}@{uu} a word: Click on the Decode/Encode toggle gadget, enter the
 desired word into the phone number entry gadget and press start.  The
 result is displayed in the listview gadget.
@endnode

